Lynsey Sharp is determined to be a part of a new golden age of British athletics after targeting medal success at the World Championships and Olympics over the next two years.

The 24-year-old Scot won 800 metres silver at the European Championships in Zurich, just missing out on defending her title from Helsinki two years ago despite setting a personal best and a new Scottish record.

The Euros were a huge success for the British contingent, with the team finishing top of the medals table with 12 golds, five silver and six bronze.

