Sharp, who also won Commonwealth Games silver at Glasgow 2014, is now determined to build on that and has set her sights on podium finishes at the next two major events in the athletics calendar.

The Loughbrough-based athlete has also targeted Dame Kelly Holmes’ British record.

‘Now that the Commonwealth Games and Europeans are out the way, the World Championships (in 2015) and the 2016 Olympics come into focus,’ said Sharp, who will be helping Radio 1 DJ Greg James prepare for the Bupa Great North Run next month.

